This paper discusses bias in data used to train machine learning models in the financial services sector, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a trusted model-lifecycle management platform, which involves the use of deep learning techniques to protect data privacy and enable secure sharing of sensitive personal information, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography (cs.CY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper addresses fairness in the use of financial instruments and services, which could be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
